<HEADLINE>Park sets sights on good business Scottish Enterprise Tayside has invested more than #900,000 over the past two years in buying a</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>BILL SINCLAIR</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Features</ARTICLETYPE>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>975241253</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Scottish Enterprise Trust envisages that the Perth Business Park at Glasgow
Road, immediately opposite the swimming pool and ice-rink complex, will
eventually accommodate a total of 100,000 sq.ft of office space in a mixture of
one and two-storey buildings, with plenty of car parking.
As well as a new road through the site, street lighting, electricity, gas,
water, telephone and drainage services were installed to each plot.
Landscaping and tree-planting has also been carried out to enhance the quality
of the site, and more landscaping is planned for each plot when building is
complete.
The opening of Robertson House in the new Perth Business Park heralded the
arrival of a major new force on the Tayside property scene.
This purpose-built, multiple occupancy building is the first major development
in Tayside by construction and development company Robertson of Elgin Ltd, and
the first speculative office development in central Perth for several years.
It provides 10,000 sq.ft of open-plan accommodation on two floors, with each
floor capable of sub-division into four separate units. A total of 40 parking
spaces has been provided.
David Sawyer, chairman of Scottish Enterprise Tayside, performed the opening
ceremony in the #1m development, and a ceremonial key was presented to Colin
Anderson, manager of the Perth office of Chartered Trust plc, the development's
first tenants.
Mr Robertson said: ``Robertson House is a major step in our overall strategy
for organic and geographical growth. We see a number of construction and
development opportunities in the Tayside area, and our base in Perth gives us
an excellent platform from which to continue our growth.''
Mr Anderson of Chartered Trust said: ``It was almost eight years since we
opened a Perth office, with a major increase in business and a workforce
expanded to 13, and new premises were a must to keep pace with this growth, and
they had to be more accessible than our previous offices.
``I am pleased to say we have found attractive modern premises at Perth
Business Park which are both spacious and accessible. Most important was the
open-plan accommodation which we found was at a premium in central Perth.''
As well as Chartered Trust, Robertson themselves will establish their Tayside
office in one unit of the new development, and there is strong interest in the
remaining space, with further tenants expected to be announced soon.
Scottish Enterprise Tayside developed the Perth Business Park for exactly this
kind of project, and assisted Robertson with its development.
Mr Sawyer said: ``Perth Business Park constitutes an important step towards
freeing development in Perth from its present constraints and helping the city
to fulfil its undoubted potential to prosper as a key business centre for
Tayside.
``That a company of the calibre of Robertson has been quick to seize upon the
opportunities afforded by a presence in Perth Business Park is surely an
encouraging omen.''
As well as Robertson House, another five out of nine plots on the development
are now spoken for. Robertson themselves are planning a similar block next
door, while work has also begun on a further two 9000 sq.ft blocks nearby.
The Traders restaurant development opposite Robertson House is almost finished,
and site investigations for a general practice surgery are under way on a fifth
plot.
Perth-based chartered surveyors Bidwells has been appointed by Scottish
Enterprise Tayside as selling agents for the Perth Business Park, and also
appointed by Robertson as letting agents for Robertson House.
Bidwells partner Gilmour Strang said: ``The scheme provides much-needed modern,
high-specification office accommodation in Perth, and the location is an
obvious attraction for many companies and their staffs, who recognise the
considerable benefits of being in the city centre, within easy walking distance
of shops and recreational facilities.
``It is the only centrally-located modern office accommodation available within
the city centre, with on-site car-parking space and yet within a convenient
five-minute drive of the motorway network.''
</TEXT>
