<DATE>951123</DATE>
<HEADLINE>NHS trust names new finance chief</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>12</PAGE>
<FLAG>NEWS DIGEST</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>975241259</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
HIGHLAND Communities NHS Trust - which faces a #1.8m deficit this year - has
appointed Mrs Helen Masters as its new director of finance.
Mrs Masters was formerly the deputy director of finance with Bradford Hospitals
NHS Trust which she joined in 1992 from the National Audit Office.
Island airlift
AN accountant with Western Isles Council who suffered serious spinal injuries
after a fall was airlifted to Glasgow's Southern General Hospital yesterday. Mr
Robert O'Gorman, 45, was found at the foot of some scaffolding at his home in
Seaview Terrace, Stornoway, on Tuesday.
Turkey call
GLASGOW-based Animal Concern yesterday called for an end to the traditional
turkey dinner at Christmas. Spokesman Mr John Robins said: ``Most of these
birds are reared in cruel factory farms. Have a cruelty free Christmas this
year and avoid turkey.''
Chapel plan
THE family chapel of the Colquhoun Clan, near Rossdhu House on Loch Lomondside,
is to be restored. Dumbarton District Council yesterday approved a plan from
Sir Ivar Colquhoun's Luss Estates Company for the refurbishment of St Mary's
Chapel - which dates back to the twelfth century.
Butcher's raided
DETECTIVES are investigating a raid on Pows Butchers shop in Sandbed, Hawick,
in which thieves stole a safe containing almost #500 in cash.
Council sacking
BERWICKSHIRE District Council has sacked its museum services officer Mr Jeff
Taylor following a disciplinary hearing into his conduct for alleged
irregularities in working practices. He was suspended earlier in the year.
</TEXT>
