<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH951123-000043</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951123-000043</DOCID>
<DATE>951123</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Golden line-up for Festival</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>ALAN HUNTER</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975241266</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TOP artists and musicians from all over the world are lined up for next year's
Edinburgh International Festival, its 50th anniversary.
Preliminary details of the 1996 programme were announced yesterday for the
three-week event which will be staged from August 11 to 31.
It will include Houston Grand Opera, the Martha Graham Dance Company, the
Theatre de la Monnale de Bruxelles, and San Francisco Ballet.
World famous orchestras will also feature including the New York Philharmonic,
the Russian National Orchestra, the Oslo Philharmonic, the Cleveland Orchestra,
the Orchestra of the Eighteenth Century, and the Hanover Band.
The programme also boasts productions by Robert Wilson, Robert Lepage, and
Peter Stein, and appearances by some of    the world's leading conductors,
including Sir Charles Mackerras, and Donald Runnicles.
Artists include Alfred Brendel, Barbara Bonney, Renee Fleming, Richard Goode,
Galina Gorchakova, the Lindsay Quartet, Quatuor Mosalques, Miranda Richardson,
Andras Schiff, and Bryn Terfel.
The next festival will also celebrate the 50th Fringe and film events, with a
number of joint events planned, including an exhibition about the three
festivals at the City Art Centre.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH951123-000044</DOCNO>
