Powderhall stadium
ORGANISERS of the ``Hands Off Powderhall Evermore'' campaign are claiming a
major boost in their bid to prevent the 107-year-old Edinburgh stadium being
demolished. The group conducted a survey of 211 local residents and claim that
161 (76.3%) are in favour of keeping the speedway and greyhound stadium. Only
20 (9.5%) said they wanted the proposed housing and office development, while
30 (14.2%) were undecided.
Planning officials meet next month to consider the housing and office
application.
