Cricket
AUSTRALIAN state side Queensland were 277 for seven at the end of the first day
of their four-day match against tourists Sri Lanka in Mackay
yesterday.Quick-scoring batsman Andrew Symonds smashed an unbeaten 73 from 75
balls to steer a Queensland revival after they had been 44 for three.
Tennis
TIM Henman's recent good form continued yesterday when he beat seventh-seeded
Frederic Fetterlein in the first round of the ATP Challenger tournament in
Andorra. The Dane, who at No.85 in the world is ranked 14 places above the
British No.2, was losing 6-4, 4-1 when he surprisingly pulled out, claiming he
was ill.
