<DATE>951123</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Mailer through</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>34</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975241290</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ONLY two Scots remain in the men's singles for day one of the Scottish Open
proper. Most hopefuls fell at the first hurdle when confronted with a top-class
international field at the Kelvin Hall.
Former Scottish champion Jim Mailer was the sole survivor of the men's singles
pre-qualifying and will join current national champion Bruce Flockhart in the
main draw.
Stirling's Mailer put out fellow Scot Alan Gooding by 15-2, 15-1 and followed
up with a 15-2, 15-7 victory over Yannick Gosselin of Canada.
Mailer will have his work cut out against former European champion and English
No.1 Darren Hall in the first round, but Flockhart should progress at the
expense of Jean Francois Mercier of Canada.
The women fared worse, with only Anne Gibson, who was given direct entry, ining
up in the singles today. Gillian Martin was a surprise casualty, going down to
Pernille Harder of Denmark in three games 11-4, 2-11, 4-11. Qualifying Scots:
Men's singles - J Mailer (Scotland) beat A Gooding (Scotland) 15-2, 15-1;
Mailer beat Y Gosselin (Canada) 15-2, 15-7.
Men's doubles - B Flockhart and C Johnston (Scotland) beat G Simpson and B
Sutherland (Scotland) 15-2, 15-0; Flockhart and Johnston beat Y Gosselin and S
Methot (Canada) 15-7, 15-6; Flockhart and Johnston beat D Forbes and R
Lethbridge (Scotland) 15-10, 15-10; D Gilmour and G Haldane (Scotland) beat G
Brockie (Scotland) and T Sorensen (Denmark) 15-4, 15-0: Gilmour and Haldane
beat C Dow and I Nixon (Scotland) 15-8, 15-2; L Dewart and A Dillon (Scotland)
beat B Hogg and B Kinnaird (Scotland) 15-9, 15-11.
Women's doubles - L McCallum and L Robertson (Scotland) beat K SNeddon and A
Thain (Scotland) 15-6, 15-8; McCallum and Robertson wo, H Blair and K Graham
(Scotland) scr.
Mixed doubles - D Murray and C Tedman (Scotland) beat G Simpson and K Sneddon
15-7, 17-18, 15-2; B Sutherland and H Blair wo, D Grieve and J Grieve
(Scotland) scr.
</TEXT>
