<TEXT>
No inquiry on
Lloyds-TSB
THE proposed merger between Lloyds Bank and TSB Group will not be referred to
the Monopolies and Mergers Commission, it was announced yesterday.
Trade and Industry Secretary Ian Lang said he had decided not to order an
inquiry by the MMC in accordance with the recommendation of the Director
General of Fair Trading.
The finance union BIFU, which fears reduced customer choice after hundreds of
branch closures and thousands of job cuts, had called for an MMC probe.
The merger is still subject to approval.
Housing deal
WESTMINSTER Health Care, Britain's second biggest private nursing home group,
has entered a #46m joint venture with Holiday Retirement Corporation to acquire
Peveral, the UK's largest manager of private sheltered housing.
Unichem move
UNICHEM  is merging its Portuguese wholesaling business with those of Alliance
Sante, a leading pharmaceutical wholesaler in southern Europe.
Medeva buys
MEDEVA is buying the Swiss gastro-intestinal drugs firm Tillotts Pharma for
#10.1m.
</TEXT>
