<HEADLINE>Healthy FKI is on lookout</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>Andrew Wilson</BYLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>21</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975241306</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ENGINEER FKI is on the lookout for more acquisitions. Chairman Jeff Whalley
said yesterday he was in discussions but there was nothing firm on the
immediate horizon, writes ANDREW WILSON.
Thanks to the #137m rights issue in June, the company has a cash balance of
#38m as well as a reputation as a shrewd purchaser.
In the six months to September, pre-tax profits rose 26.7% to #39.4m on
turnover 5.3% higher at #429m to leave group margins improved from 9% to 10.4%.
The interim dividend has been raised 10% to 2.2p.
</TEXT>
