<HEADLINE>Euro-rebel wins MP award</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975241361</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FORMER Tory Euro-rebel Richard Shepherd yesterday was named as the Spectator
magazine's Parliamentarian of Year.
Presenting the award at a lunch at the Savoy Hotel, London, the magazine's
editor Frank Johnson highlighted the consistency of Mr Shepherd (Aldridge
Brownhills) in defying the Government after becoming one of nine Conservative
MPs to lose the party whip.
Among the other awards, Home Secretary Michael Howard was named Debater of the
Year for his ``rout'' of Labour's Jack Straw in the recent prison service
debate; former Tory Party leadership challenger John Redwood was Back Bencher
of the Year; Liberal Democrat leader Paddy Ashdown was Campaigner of the Year
for his efforts to change Government policy on Bosnia; Labour's new Chief Whip
Donald Dewar was Member to Watch; and there were special awards for services in
the House of Lords for Baroness Seear and Baroness Trumpington.
</TEXT>
