<HEADLINE>Agnosticism</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>18</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>correspondence</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975241362</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
I SUSPECT the Episcopal Bishop of Edinburgh's gradual retreat from the standard
interpretation of the Bible is due to his embarrassment, as an intellectual, at
holding views which depend on the revelation of scripture, rather than that of
philosophical inquiry, for validity (November 16).
Why doesn't he take the plunge and join me in the agnostic camp?
Paul Goggins,
46 Dumbarton Road,
Bowling.
</TEXT>
