<TEXT>
PETER GRANT, aged 60, the man credited with turning rock music into a global
business, has died from a heart attack, it was announced last night. He managed
Led Zeppelin from the late 1960s and throughout the 1970s. He leaves a son
Warren and daughter Helen.
