<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>16</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Obituary</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>975241379</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FORMER Scottish amateur    flyweight champion and international competitor Alex
``Spango'' Hunter from Dunfermline has died suddenly. A Commonwealth
bronze-medallist at the 1966 games in Kingston, Jamaica, Hunter collapsed while
refereeing a bout in the Eastern District amateur championships in Edinburgh on
Sunday evening. The 53-year-old official slumped to the floor halfway through
the contest, featuring Geoff Simpson and Matthew Fleming, and though rushed to
hospital did not regain consciousness.
</TEXT>
